OL,6,FJudge Lady Drummond told him: "You
OL,7,Frecognise yourself that your fraud has
OL,8,Fcaused harm.
OL,10,F"It is likely to have impacted on the
OL,11,Fpeople whose identities have been
OL,12,Fstolen and their families who to learn
OL,13,Fof this.
OL,15,F"The sentence I impose is for the
OL,16,Fprotection of the public, to punish
OL,17,Fyou for the crimes, to mark society's
OL,18,Fdisapproval, deterrence and your
OL,19,Frehabilitation.
